cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.NE 

The paper introduces a new method for exploration in reinforcement learning (RL) agents by utilizing optical flow estimation from computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which covers topics related to RL. The paper also utilizes computer vision techniques, specifically optical flow estimation, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper introduces a new intrinsic curiosity module, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses hyper-parameters used in the training phase, which could place it in the category of cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper utilizes deep neural networks, which suggests that it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
